## GAS file → domain mapping

| GAS file | Domain | Vercel env var |
|----------|--------|----------------|
| `TLCG_CORE_BACKEND.gs` | Shared/Auth | `TLCG_CORE_BACKEND_URL` (fallback: `TLCGROUP_BACKEND_URL`) |
| `TLCG_P2P_BACKEND.gs` | P2P — Mua hàng | `TLCG_P2P_BACKEND_URL` (fallback: `PAYMENT_REQUEST_BACKEND_URL`) |
| `TLCG_CASH_BACKEND.gs` | Cash & Admin | `TLCG_CASH_BACKEND_URL` (fallback: `VOUCHER_BACKEND_URL`) |
| `TLCG_O2C_BACKEND.gs` | O2C — Bán hàng (future) | `TLCG_O2C_BACKEND_URL` |

## When editing this flow

- `BACKEND_URL` in `purchase_request.html` must stay as **`/api/voucher`** — never hardcode a direct GAS exec URL.
- To rotate the P2P deployment URL, update `TLCG_P2P_BACKEND_URL` in Vercel Dashboard → Settings → Environment Variables.
- Align **`Goods-KTT`** sheet headers with `seedGoods` column names (`Items`, `Min. Order`, `Status`, `Category`, `Unit`, `Specification`, `CUKCUK/QBO Code`).
- `Purchase_Request_History` sheet is auto-created on first submit if missing.
- PR numbers are **client-generated** (localStorage counter per day). GAS does not enforce uniqueness — do not rely on them as globally unique IDs.
